The '''black-streaked scimitar babbler''' ('''''Erythrogenys gravivox''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Timaliidae]]. It is found in China, [[Laos]], [[Myanmar]] and [[Vietnam]], where its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />

